    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "I just went to check the [extensions index](https://github.com/ipython/ipython/wiki/Extensions-Index), and all the `%install_ext` instructions have been replaced with `%<deprecated command>`. I'm not very happy about this: it's punishing users rather than developers, and it doesn't give them any clear alternative to get those extensions that aren't on pip. I'm going to revert that.\r\n\r\nI'm fine with deprecating this and removing it from docs, but I think we should leave it working for quite a long time."
  },
