    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "I don't think a pip-installable option can work without having people do `%load_ext install_ext` first, and that gets a bit ridiculous. From the relative lack of issues complaining that we broke things, we got away with this, but I think it was a sadly cavalier attitude to extension authors to remove functionality. It's a long way from Linux's *don't break userspace*."
